results.name: Number of partitions of n into distinct parts 5*k+2 or 5*k+3.
comment: Convolution of A281271 and A281272. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jan 18 2017
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000 (terms 0..250 from Reinhard Zumkeller)
formula: a(n) ~ exp(sqrt(2*n/15)*Pi) / (2*30^(1/4)*n^(3/4)) * (1 - (3*sqrt(15/2)/(8*Pi) + 11*Pi/(60*sqrt(30))) / sqrt(n)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jan 18 2017, extended Jan 24 2017
mathematica: nmax = 100; CoefficientList[Series[Product[(1 + x^(5*k - 2))*(1 + x^(5*k - 3)), {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jan 18 2017 *)
program: p (k:ks) m = if m < k then 0 else p ks (m - k) + p ks m
